From: Jean Noel Cordenner <jean-noel.cordenner@bull.net>

This patch converts the 32-bit i_version in the generic inode to a 64-bit
i_version field.

Signed-off-by: Mingming Cao <cmm@us.ibm.com>
Signed-off-by: Jean Noel Cordenner <jean-noel.cordenner@bull.net>
Signed-off-by: Kalpak Shah <kalpak@clusterfs.com>

Index: linux-2.6.22-rc6/include/linux/fs.h
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.22-rc6.orig/include/linux/fs.h	2007-07-03 17:48:45.000000000 -0700
+++ linux-2.6.22-rc6/include/linux/fs.h	2007-07-03 17:52:38.000000000 -0700
@@ -538,7 +538,7 @@ struct inode {
 	uid_t			i_uid;
 	gid_t			i_gid;
 	dev_t			i_rdev;
-	unsigned long		i_version;
+	u64			i_version;
 	loff_t			i_size;
 #ifdef __NEED_I_SIZE_ORDERED
 	seqcount_t		i_size_seqcount;
